org.openstreetmap.osm.data.osmbin.v1_0
Class AbstractEntityFile

java.lang.Object
  org.openstreetmap.osm.data.osmbin.FixedRecordFile
      org.openstreetmap.osm.data.osmbin.v1_0.AbstractEntityFile
Direct Known Subclasses:
NodesFile, RelationsFile, WaysFile
public abstract class AbstractEntityFile
extends FixedRecordFile

(c) 2008 by here
We assume that all record start with the element-id (long) stored as int and that Integer.MIN_VALUE denoted an unused record.
We also allow reading and writing attributes of entities. For this we first parse the taglist of the Entity#getTagList() and split values for tags that are too long for a fixed size slot into multiple slots. Then we store them in the format:

  • (short) id of tag-name, or Short.MIN_VALUE for an empty slot or Short.MIN_VALUE + 1 for a continuation of the value in the last slot
  • tag-characters in UTF16 padded to the length of the fixed-size-record with the Java-Char -value 0. This padding is removed uppon reading.

Author:
Marcus Wolschon
